# ── TLS issuer partial: INTERNAL mode (primary) ──────────────────────────────
# Caddy's built-in local CA signs every suite hostname. ZERO dependency on any
# public service: no public DNS, no ACME, no Let's Encrypt. Fully self-contained.
#
# Root/intermediate are generated on first boot and stored in the /data volume at:
#   /data/caddy/pki/authorities/local/root.crt   (distribute this — see BUILD.md)
#   /data/caddy/pki/authorities/local/intermediate.crt
#
# Names are served with internal certs issued on demand as SNIs arrive. If the
# pinned Caddy will not sign the wildcard subject directly, on-demand per-name
# issuance covers it (internal CA has no rate limits). See BUILD.md §"internal mode".
# Stage-5 hardening: pin an explicit, auditable TLS-1.2 floor (1.2 min, 1.3 max). This EQUALS
# Caddy's secure-by-default (min tls1.2), so it is behaviourally a no-op but makes the floor
# explicit/reviewable. It lives INSIDE the tls directive (the only mode-specific content), so the
# Option-C "byte-identical except the issuer partial" invariant holds — the identical `protocols`
# line is in both partials. Ciphers/curves are intentionally NOT overridden: Caddy's defaults are
# AEAD-only + post-quantum (X25519MLKEM768); pinning a list would age badly and disable that. Do
# NOT add `issuer internal` here — mixing the `internal` shorthand with the `issuer` subdirective
# is a load error. (Stage-5 research)
tls internal {
	protocols tls1.2 tls1.3
}
